{"batch":"api_surface_coherence","batch_index":17,"assessments":{"api_surface_coherence":72.8},"dimension_notes":{"api_surface_coherence":{"evidence":["The shared helper layer in nba_pbp_utils.py mixes several API styles: fetch_playbyplay_payload() raises HTTP/JSON exceptions on failure, load_game_dataframe() forwards those exceptions, extract_team_context() raises ValueError for malformed game data, while actions_to_dataframe() and build_valid_possessions() return empty DataFrames for missing/invalid input instead of failing fast.","The two season pipelines expose the same workflow through different public contracts. calculate_wmi_rawseason_2010_11_to_2023_24.py uses fetch_game_json_with_retry() and process_game() with string status tags like \"ok\"/\"missing\" and dict payloads, but calculate_wmi_rawseason_2024_25.py uses load_game_dataframe_with_retry() and build_possession_table_for_game() with exceptions plus None return values for non-usable games.","extract_team_context() returns an unnamed 3-tuple whose elements are consumed positionally in several shapes across callers, such as team_id_to_tricode, opponent_id, team_ids in build_possession_model_table_okc_mil.py and _, opponent_id, team_ids in calculate_wmi_rawseason_2024_25.py, so callers must remember tuple order instead of relying on a named result type.","Similar public entry points also accept different input forms for the same domain step: parse_possessions() expects a prebuilt play-by-play DataFrame plus an optional game_id, build_table() and build_def_foul_context() accept a game_id and fetch internally, and calculate_wmi_rawgame() accepts an already-shaped possession table DataFrame. That makes the pipeline hard to compose consistently without reading each implementation."],"impact_scope":"subsystem","fix_scope":"multi_file_refactor","confidence":"high"}},"issues":[{"dimension":"api_surface_coherence","identifier":"season_pipeline_error_contract_drift","summary":"The two season pipelines expose incompatible fetch/error contracts for the same workflow.","related_files":["calculate_wmi_rawseason_2010_11_to_2023_24.py","calculate_wmi_rawseason_2024_25.py","nba_pbp_utils.py"],"evidence":["calculate_wmi_rawseason_2010_11_to_2023_24.py:83-103 returns (status, payload) from fetch_game_json_with_retry(), using string sentinels like \"ok\" and \"missing\".","calculate_wmi_rawseason_2010_11_to_2023_24.py:152-170 wraps that again in a dict with another \"status\" field, so callers branch on status strings.","calculate_wmi_rawseason_2024_25.py:26-41 instead retries load_game_dataframe() by catching RETRYABLE_PIPELINE_ERRORS and re-raising on exhaustion.","calculate_wmi_rawseason_2024_25.py:44-73 then uses None as the signal for a non-usable game, while collect_parallel_tables() also catches exceptions separately at lines 109-116."],"suggestion":"Pick one public contract for game loading across the pipeline, such as a typed result object or a single exception-based API, and route both season scripts through that shared boundary so callers do not have to remember different failure shapes.","confidence":"high","impact_scope":"subsystem","fix_scope":"multi_file_refactor","root_cause_cluster":"pipeline_contract_drift"},{"dimension":"api_surface_coherence","identifier":"tuple_based_team_context_api","summary":"extract_team_context() exposes a positional tuple that makes callers rely on argument order.","related_files":["nba_pbp_utils.py","step2_build_possessions.py","build_possession_model_table_okc_mil.py","calculate_wmi_rawseason_2024_25.py"],"evidence":["nba_pbp_utils.py:93-101 returns tuple[dict[int, str], dict[int, int], list[int]] with no named fields.","step2_build_possessions.py:30 unpacks all three values positionally into team_id_to_tricode, opponent_id, team_ids.","calculate_wmi_rawseason_2024_25.py:52 discards the first item with _, opponent_id, team_ids, showing that callers only need parts of the tuple but still must remember its order.","build_possession_model_table_okc_mil.py:22 and categorize_defensive_fouls_okc_mil.py:23 repeat the same positional unpacking pattern, so a changed return order would silently break multiple modules."],"suggestion":"Replace the raw tuple with a small named result type, such as a dataclass or NamedTuple with fields like team_id_to_tricode, opponent_id, and team_ids, so callers can access only the fields they need by name.","confidence":"high","impact_scope":"subsystem","fix_scope":"multi_file_refactor","root_cause_cluster":"unnamed_boundary_data"},{"dimension":"api_surface_coherence","identifier":"pipeline_steps_take_mixed_input_shapes","summary":"Similar pipeline steps alternate between raw game IDs and prebuilt DataFrames as public inputs.","related_files":["step2_build_possessions.py","build_possession_model_table_okc_mil.py","categorize_defensive_fouls_okc_mil.py","calculate_wmi_rawgame_okc_mil.py"],"evidence":["step2_build_possessions.py:23-104 defines parse_possessions(pbp_df, game_id=...) and expects the caller to provide a play-by-play DataFrame.","build_possession_model_table_okc_mil.py:20-84 defines build_table(game_id) and performs its own fetch internally for a nearby transformation step.","categorize_defensive_fouls_okc_mil.py:21-104 follows the same game_id-based style, while calculate_wmi_rawgame_okc_mil.py:9-46 switches again to calculate_wmi_rawgame(df) over an already-shaped possession table.","Because these functions sit on adjacent pipeline stages but expose different boundary shapes, a developer cannot predict whether a helper wants identifiers, raw actions, or DataFrames without opening the file."],"suggestion":"Define one composable pipeline convention for public helpers, for example pure transformation functions that take DataFrames plus thin CLI wrappers that fetch/load files, and apply it consistently across these scripts.","confidence":"medium","impact_scope":"subsystem","fix_scope":"multi_file_refactor","root_cause_cluster":"pipeline_contract_drift"}],"retrospective":{"root_causes":["The project evolved as several standalone scripts, so each script introduced its own boundary style instead of reusing one shared public contract.","Shared helpers mostly standardize data logic, but not the shape of success/failure results or the kinds of inputs public functions should accept."],"likely_symptoms":["season_pipeline_error_contract_drift","pipeline_steps_take_mixed_input_shapes"],"possible_false_positives":[]}}
